comments.content: That's what I thought (Hadrain). It is part of a business card. I've just been told it was designed in the early 80s, when I was an infant, and was probably phototype.
Which, now that I think about it, could mean it was Hanseatic.
MarcC wins, I've purchased Swiss 924. Thanks
Yeah there's not a big difference between Hadrian and swiss, but we could see on the letter E
